        "content": "<p>I am exploring how to test module functions. It seems that kunit_tests doesn't work when it comes to kernel module. Then I tried to call test function when module init. But I found it hard to call test when I impl InplaceModule for my own Module. Following is my code: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RustMM</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PinInit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Rust Memory Management (init)</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RMMGlobalAllocator</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// For now, we just add one allocator(id: 0) for host process.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">insert_allocator</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_mm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">try_pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new_spinlock</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// rust_mm.test();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">rust_mm</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
